## Shell

{{- if eq .chezmoi.os "windows" }}
- Prefer the PowerShell tool over Bash, regardless of what the environment
  block reports.
{{- end }}
- For long-running commands, use `Bash` with `run_in_background: true`
  instead of piping through `head`/`tail`/`Select-Object`. The harness
  captures stdout/stderr to an output file (path in the tool result) and
  notifies on exit — then `Read` the file. Spot-check the live file if you
  suspect a hang; don't busy-poll.
- Pair every background `Bash` with a stall-detector `Monitor` — the Bash
  `timeout` only bounds the foreground call, so backgrounded processes can
  hang silently for the rest of the session. Sketch (polls output size,
  emits when it doesn't grow for 60s; stop with `TaskStop` after the task
  completes):
  ```
  prev=-1
  while true; do
    sleep 60
    cur=$(stat -c %s <output-file> 2>/dev/null || echo 0)
    [ "$cur" = "$prev" ] && echo "STALLED: no output for 60s ($cur bytes)"
    prev=$cur
  done
  ```
- Use `Monitor` directly for per-occurrence streaming (e.g., every ERROR
  line): pass a command whose stdout lines are the events
  (`tail -f log | grep --line-buffered -E "ERROR|FAIL"`). Monitor does not
  auto-tail files.

## LSP

- Prefer LSP over Read/Grep for symbol-level code navigation:
  - Finding a definition: `goToDefinition` instead of grepping the symbol name
  - Finding all usages: `findReferences` instead of grepping — avoids false positives
    from comments, strings, and same-named identifiers in unrelated scopes
  - Understanding file structure: `documentSymbol` instead of reading the entire file
  - Finding interface implementations: `goToImplementation` instead of grepping
  - Tracing call chains: `incomingCalls`/`outgoingCalls` instead of manual grep
  - Getting type info or docs: `hover` instead of reading source to infer types
  - Finding a symbol across the workspace: `workspaceSymbol` instead of Glob + Grep
- Fall back to Read/Grep for non-symbol searches: string literals, config values,
  comments, regex patterns, or files without LSP server support
- After editing code, check for `<new-diagnostics>` in system reminders — the LSP
  server pushes diagnostics automatically. Fix any errors or warnings before proceeding

## Agent Teams

- When I ask for an "agent team", "team of agents", or "swarm", always use the
  `TeamCreate` tool to create a coordinated team with shared task lists —
  never substitute regular `Agent` subagents. Use `Agent` with `team_name` to
  spawn teammates into the team.

## Worktree Sessions

- After `wt switch --create <branch>` / `wt switch <branch>`
  / `wt switch pr:<num>`, immediately call `EnterWorktree` with the
  printed path to switch the session into the worktree. This moves cwd,
  status line, file resolution, and git context.
- Use `ExitWorktree { action: "keep" }` to return to the original session
  directory. `ExitWorktree` cannot remove worktrunk-managed worktrees (they
  were entered by path, not created by Claude) — use
  `wt remove <branch>` to delete.
- NEVER call `EnterWorktree` with `name`. That creates a Claude-native
  worktree under `.claude/worktrees/`, bypassing worktrunk and its
  post-start bootstrap (`.local` file mirroring, `pnpm install`, `.vs/`
  carry-over). Always create via `wt switch --create`, then enter
  by path.

